sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant TG as Telegram Bot
    participant Agent as Zico Agent<br/>(staking_agent)
    participant Backend as Lido Service<br/>(:3004)
    participant Miniapp as MiniApp Frontend
    participant Wallet as Thirdweb Wallet
    participant Lido as Lido Protocol<br/>(Ethereum)

    User->>TG: "I want to stake 1 ETH"
    TG->>Agent: Forward message
    Agent->>Agent: Semantic routing -> STAKING intent
    Agent->>Agent: Collect staking parameters (amount=1, action=stake)
    Agent-->>TG: staking_intent_ready + metadata
    TG-->>User: "Stake 1 ETH via Lido for ~3.5% APY" + [Review] button

    User->>Miniapp: Opens staking page
    Miniapp->>Backend: GET /staking/apy
    Backend-->>Miniapp: APY: 3.5%

    User->>Miniapp: Confirms stake
    Miniapp->>Backend: POST /staking/prepare {amount: 1 ETH}
    Backend-->>Miniapp: PreparedTx {to: lido, data: submit(), value: 1 ETH}

    Miniapp->>Wallet: Sign transaction
    Wallet->>Lido: submit{value: 1 ETH}()
    Lido-->>Wallet: ~0.95 stETH minted to user
    Wallet-->>Miniapp: tx receipt

    Miniapp->>Miniapp: Track via Gateway API
    Miniapp-->>User: "Staked! Receiving ~0.95 stETH"

    Note over User,Lido: Unstake flow: queue (7 days) or instant (with fee)
